## By Category

### Meta-Skills (Force Multipliers)

These skills help you create and improve other skills.

| Skill | Purpose | Best For | Dependencies |
|-------|---------|----------|--------------|
| [skill_drafting](SKILL/skill_template.md) | Turn messy intent into structured skills | Creating new skills quickly | None |
| [skill_critiquing](SKILL/SKILL.skill_critiquing.md) | Review and refine existing skills | Quality assurance and improvement | skill_drafting (optional) |

### Repository & Onboarding Skills

Essential for understanding and analyzing codebases, especially useful for new projects.

| Skill | Purpose | Best For | Typical Runtime |
|-------|---------|----------|-----------------|
| [repo_recon](SKILL/SKILL.repo_recon.md) | Map structure, tech stack, and risks | New project onboarding | 5-15 minutes |
| [security_scan](SKILL/SKILL.security_scan.md) | Find vulnerabilities and security issues | Security audits and compliance | 10-20 minutes |
| [test_survey](SKILL/SKILL.test_survey.md) | Evaluate test coverage and quality | Quality assessment | 5-10 minutes |
| [deps_audit](SKILL/SKILL.deps_audit.md) | Audit dependencies for health | Dependency management | 5-15 minutes |

### Code Quality Skills

For ongoing maintenance, improvement, and quality assurance.

| Skill | Purpose | Best For | Complexity |
|-------|---------|----------|------------|
| [refactor_plan](SKILL/SKILL.refactor_plan.md) | Plan safe refactoring strategies | Major code changes | Advanced |
| [perf_audit](SKILL/SKILL.perf_audit.md) | Identify performance bottlenecks | Optimization efforts | Advanced |
| [api_design](SKILL/SKILL.api_design.md) | Review and improve API design | API development | Advanced |

