## Pipeline Integration

### FLOW.onboard.yaml
Uses: repo_recon, security_scan, test_survey, deps_audit
Purpose: Complete new project onboarding

### FLOW.quality_audit.yaml
Uses: repo_recon, test_survey, perf_audit, api_design, refactor_plan
Purpose: Comprehensive code quality assessment

### FLOW.skill_pipeline.yaml
Uses: skill_drafting, skill_critiquing
Purpose: Meta-skill development workflow

## Skill Dependencies

### Independent Skills (No Dependencies)
- All skills are self-contained and can be used independently

### Complementary Skills (Work Well Together)
- repo_recon + security_scan (comprehensive analysis)
- test_survey + refactor_plan (quality improvement)
- deps_audit + perf_audit (performance optimization)

### Sequential Skills (Best Used in Order)
- skill_drafting → skill_critiquing (skill development workflow)
- repo_recon → refactor_plan (analysis → action)
- security_scan → deps_audit (security → dependencies)

## Usage Patterns

### Quick Analysis (Under 10 minutes)
- repo_recon (5 min)
- test_survey (5 min)
- deps_audit (5 min)

### Comprehensive Assessment (15-30 minutes)
- FLOW.onboard.yaml (15-25 min)
- FLOW.quality_audit.yaml (20-40 min)

### Custom Workflows (Variable)
- skill_drafting + skill_critiquing (10-20 min)
- Custom skill combinations (depends on skills used)

